#### 1B. CSS Techniques for Sci-Fi Aesthetics

| Technique | Implementation | Key CSS Properties |
|-----------|---------------|-------------------|
| **Neon glow text** | Stack multiple `text-shadow` values with increasing blur radius, same hue | `text-shadow: 0 0 7px #fff, 0 0 10px #fff, 0 0 21px #fff, 0 0 42px #0fa, 0 0 82px #0fa` |
| **Neon glow borders/cards** | Layered `box-shadow` with color-matched values | `box-shadow: 0 0 5px cyan, 0 0 20px cyan, inset 0 0 5px cyan` |
| **Holographic/iridescent effects** | Layered `linear-gradient` + `conic-gradient` with `mix-blend-mode: color-dodge` and OKLCH colors | `background`, `mix-blend-mode`, `filter` |
| **Animated gradient backgrounds** | Oversized `background-size: 200% 200%` with keyframe animation shifting `background-position` | `@keyframes shimmer`, `background-position` |
| **Grid/cyber line patterns** | CSS `background-image` using repeating-linear-gradient for grid overlays | `repeating-linear-gradient(0deg, rgba(0,255,255,.1) 1px, transparent 1px)` |
| **Glassmorphism** | `backdrop-filter: blur()` + semi-transparent backgrounds + colored borders | `backdrop-filter`, `background: rgba()`, `border` |
| **Glitch effects** | `clip-path` animation + offset pseudo-elements with color channels | `@keyframes glitch`, `clip-path`, `transform: translate()` |
| **CSS 3D transforms** | `perspective`, `rotateY`, `rotateX`, `translateZ` for depth | `transform-style: preserve-3d`, `perspective` |

**Key reference for holographic CSS**: The OpenReplay guide (https://blog.openreplay.com/creating-holographic-effects-css/) provides production-ready code using OKLCH color space, layered gradients, blend modes, and accessible motion with `prefers-reduced-motion` support.

