### 4. FREE SCI-FI CSS FRAMEWORKS AND EFFECTS

#### 4A. Dedicated Sci-Fi Frameworks

| Framework | URL | Stars | Features | License | Free? |
|-----------|-----|-------|----------|---------|-------|
| **Arwes** | https://github.com/arwes/arwes | ~1.5K | Full sci-fi UI framework with animations, sound effects, React components, cyber/space themes. Influenced by Star Citizen, Halo, NIKKE. | MIT | Yes |
| **Cybercore CSS** | https://github.com/sebyx07/cybercore-css | ~200+ | Pure CSS cyberpunk framework: neon glow borders (cyan/magenta/green), glitch effects, scanlines, terminal styling, no JS required | MIT | Yes |
| **Futuristic UI** | https://github.com/bhanustark/futuristic-ui | Newer | React component library: holographic elements, glitch text, neon buttons, circuit loaders, data stream skeletons, cyber tabs | MIT | Yes |

**Arwes -- Key Details**:
- Most mature sci-fi framework (though currently unmaintained)
- Provides animated borders, frames, sounds, and sci-fi themed components
- React v18 packages with SSR support
- Used by real projects (SoulExtract.com, RomelPerez.dev, etc.)
- Caveat: No longer actively maintained, but forkable

**Cybercore CSS -- Key Details**:
- Pure CSS, zero JavaScript dependencies
- Components: `.neon-border`, `.glitch-text`, `.scanlines`, `.terminal-window`
- Color variants: cyan, magenta, green neon
- Best fit: Lightweight cyberpunk overlay on existing site

**Futuristic UI -- Key Details**:
- React-specific with TypeScript support
- Components: GlitchText, CircuitLoader, HologramCheckbox, DataStreamSkeleton, NeonButton
- Variants: neon, hologram, circuit
- Built-in dark theme
- Caveat: React-specific (PhoneHub is vanilla JS -- would need adaptation)

