### 5. FREE ANIMATION LIBRARIES FOR SCROLL REVEALS (Summary)

| Library | Recommended Use | Size | License | Integration with Vanilla JS |
|---------|----------------|------|---------|----------------------------|
| **GSAP + ScrollTrigger** | Complex animations, pinning, scrub | ~100KB | Free standard license | Excellent -- framework agnostic |
| **Intersection Observer** | Simple reveal on scroll | 0KB | Native browser API | Native -- no library needed |
| **AOS.js** | Quick basic animations | ~6KB | MIT | Excellent |
| **Lenis** | Smooth scroll only | ~2.1KB | MIT | Excellent |
| **Sal.js** | Lightweight AOS alternative | ~3KB | MIT | Excellent |
| **Trig.js** | CSS-driven scroll animations | ~4KB | MIT | Excellent (CSS-first) |
| **Motion One** | Web Animations API | ~8KB | MIT | Excellent |
| **Locomotive Scroll** | Smooth scroll + animations | ~12KB | MIT | Good (data-attributes) |

**Best stack for PhoneHub**: **Lenis** + **GSAP ScrollTrigger** + **Intersection Observer** for lazy-loading. This gives smooth scrolling, advanced scroll-driven animations, and native lazy-load detection.

