### 7. MONITORING / HEALTH-CHECK BOT PATTERNS

#### 7A. Free Website Monitoring Tools

| Tool | URL | What It Offers | Free Tier | Best For |
|------|-----|----------------|-----------|----------|
| **Upptime** | https://upptime.js.org/ / https://github.com/upptime/upptime | Open-source uptime monitor + status page, powered entirely by GitHub Actions, Issues, and Pages. Checks every 5 min, auto-creates GitHub issues on downtime | Completely free, unlimited | PhoneHub (GitHub Pages hosted) |
| **UptimeRobot** | https://uptimerobot.com/ | 50 monitors, 5-minute check interval, email/SMS alerts | Free (50 monitors) | General uptime monitoring |
| **Broken Link Checker Action** | https://github.com/marketplace/actions/broken-link-checker-action | GitHub Action to detect broken links in pages, auto-creates issues | Free | CI/CD link validation |
| **Broken Links Crawler** | https://github.com/marketplace/actions/broken-links-crawler | GitHub Action checking all links on a site for 403/404 errors | Free | Deep link crawling |
| **Linkinator** | https://jbeckwith.com/projects/linkinator | CLI tool + GitHub Action for scanning dead links in static/HTML files | Free (MIT) | Static site link checking |
| **Website Uptime Monitor Action** | https://github.com/marketplace/actions/website-uptime-monitor | GitHub Action: monitors uptime, logs response, creates issues when down | Free | GitHub-native monitoring |

#### 7B. Recommended Monitoring Stack for PhoneHub

Since PhoneHub is deployed via GitHub Actions to GitHub Pages:

1. **Upptime** (primary uptime monitor)
   - Fork the Upptime template repo
   - Add PhoneHub URL to config
   - GitHub Actions checks every 5 minutes
   - Auto-generates a status page on GitHub Pages
   - Creates GitHub Issues automatically on downtime
   - Completely free, open source (MIT)

2. **Broken Link Checker Action** (CI/CD integration)
   - Add to existing `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` or create separate workflow
   - Runs after each deployment
   - Reports broken links as GitHub Issues

3. **Linkinator** (development-time checking)
   - Run locally or in CI before deployment
   - Catches dead links in static HTML files
   - MIT licensed, npm installable

